<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[1]
Date: Sat, 5 Feb 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, 4 Feb 2005 Vol.18, No. 5 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/a_current.htm#Sec2>

Bluetongue in Spain: Follow-up report No. 6
-------------------------------------------
Translation of information received on 28 Jan 2005 from Dr Arnaldo Cabello
Navarro, Deputy Director General of Animal Health, Ministry of Agriculture,
Fisheries and Food, Madrid:
End of previous report period: 9 Dec 2004.
End of this report period: 27 Jan 2005.
Precise identification of agent: bluetongue virus serotype 4.
Details of new outbreaks:
[The report includes a table -- omitted here -- specifying the details of
116 outbreaks which started between 15 Oct and 23 Dec 2004 in 3 provinces
("1st administrative division"): 102 in Andalusia, 2 in Ceuta and 12 in
Extremadura. Further details in the table: Lower administrative division/
Type of epidemiological unit/ Name of the location/ Date of start of the
outbreak/ Species/ Number of animals in the outbreak/susceptible/ cases/
deaths/ destroyed/ slaughtered. All said data may be viewed to at the above
web-site. - Mod.AS]
Diagnosis:
Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Central Veterinary Laboratory, Algete
Diagnostic tests used: ELISA for antibody detection; RT-PCR.
Source of outbreaks: vectors.
Control measures undertaken:
- control of arthropods;
- partial stamping out [the total number of destroyed animals, as detailed
in the above table, was 168];
- movement control inside the country;
- zoning;
- vaccination.
Vaccination in response to the outbreaks:
1st administrative division/species/ Total number of vaccinated animals/
Details of the vaccine
Andalusia/ bov*/ 328 258/ serotype 4 monovalent live attenuated virus vaccine
[* bov should probably read ovi. - Mod.AS]
Extremadura/ ovi/ 426 246/ serotype 4 monovalent live attenuated virus vaccine
Treatment of affected animals: no.
Vaccination prohibited: no.
--
OIE Animal Health Information Department
<information.dept@oie.int>
[The affected species, as reported for each of the 116 outbreaks, were the
following: ovines 59; bovines 34; caprines 4; ovines+caprines 10;
bovines+ovines 3; ovines+caprines+bovines 6. Though not specified in the
report, it might be assumed that most if not all cases reported in bovines
and caprines were subclinical. More detailed information pertaining to this
issue could help. - Mod.AS]
